The sinner having stood a little while, began knocking again, and asking to be 
let into the kingdom of heaven. And a third voice was heard within the gates, 
saying:


So Emelyán lay down and slept. His wife roused him early next day. 'Go 
quickly,' said she, 'and finish the cathedral. Here are nails and a hammer; 
there is still enough work there for a day.'


Having seen that this, too, was not well, God decided so as to arrange things 
that man should not know the time of his death, but might die at any moment; 
and he announced this to them.
